The paper focuses on automated testing of deep neural networks, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of coverage criteria as feedback for guiding the test generation suggests a focus on software testing and verification (cs.CR), while the use of multiple tests in a batch and prioritization based on active feedback suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
